nombre: IMI B2B - Instituto de Marketing Industrial
resumen:
In IMI B2B we believe that a specific approach is necessary to address the characteristics and particularities of the Industrial / B2B (Business to Business) Marketing and Sales Strategy. We, therefore, founded an institute offering world-class knowledge and consulting for companies and associations. At the B2B Academy (www.imib2b.org/academia) it offers raining and teaching for executives and professionals in business and industries with marketing & sales responsibilities. IMI B2B organizes also events and meetings with specialists and has a club for companies and individuals to join, get part of the B2B community and participate in its development. 

IMI B2B has a strategic alliance with the prestigious Center for Business & Industrial Marketing, Georgia State University (Atlanta, USA), which ensures access and transfer of state-of-the-art know-how in its consultant services and teaching. At the moment, IMI B2B is present in Peru and Chile.

resumen:
Caban Condos Mexico is a privately owned & operated company that began in Saskatoon, Saskatchewan in 2010 under the parent company Regal Property Developments.

We operate in both Canada & Mexico specializing in custom home builds in Saskatchewan & Ocean Front Condo developments in Yucatan, Mexico. We are your trusted Canadian developer in south Mexico, with affordable ocean front prices. 

With our first project completed and sold out on the Caribbean sea in Mahahual, Mexico we are now beginning construction on a beautiful, luxurious 20 unit condomunium project in San Crisanto, Yucatan Mexico. Located just 45 minutes from the historic city of Merida, a population of 1 million people. In Merida you will find many amenities and services you are used to back home. Including Costco, Sam's Club, Starbucks, many high end shopping malls etc. Many airlines offer direct service to Merida, for Canadians WestJet now has seasonal direct flights from Toronto to Merida, and should be opening direct out of Calgary soon.

Prices starting at only $159,900 USD for 3 bedroom, 2 bath 1640 sq ft ocean front condos & $139,900 for ocean view beach villas. Penthouses feature private rooftop with own palapa bar, tv, and soaker pool. Beautiful white sand beaches and our infiniti pool will dazzle amaze you. Come find your paradise and escape here!

We are two guys from Saskatchewan, Canada building beautiful & affordable ocean front properties for you in paradise. 

Yours in paradise,

Mike Delaire & Parrish Kondra

resumen:
‚ñ† We create, launch & support highly specialized travel brands that change the world for the better. ‚ñ†

We are a global network of tourism experts, who create, launch and support highly specialized, individually branded travel services. All our services are led by passionate intrapreneurs with an extraordinary travel expertise.

‚ñ† Our Purpose ‚ñ†

In the past, journeys were pulled from the catalogues of mass-marketed travel operators. But this is changing. More and more travellers prefer unique journeys that suit their taste, interests and budget. At the same time, they look for authentic and sustainable journeys that make a positive impact on both their own life and the communities they visit.

We believe that journeys like this can not be created ‚Äúoff-the-shelf‚Äù. Only passionate specialists will be able to organise unique, authentic and responsible trips.

This is why we encourage these passionate specialists to create their own brands - while we have their back. By adding a professional framework to their expertise we create reliable yet unforgettable travel experiences.

resumen:
We work one-on-one with teachers to create incredible educational tours that meet their specific needs and budget. All Explorica tours are fully inclusive and expertly designed to immerse participants in the local culture while introducing them to the people, places and experiences that make each destination unique.

Explorica is committed to enriching students through educational travel, and that means helping teachers extend the opportunity to as many students as possible. In addition to offering the guaranteed best prices in educational travel, we also provide scholarships, need-based financial assistance, and a variety of resources to ensure that every student is able to join their classmates on the trip of a lifetime.

Explorica is a part of WorldStrides, the global leader in educational travel and experiential learning. WorldStrides was founded in 1967 to provide middle school travel programs to Washington, D.C., and has grown to provide a wide range of programs for more than 550,000 students annually to over 100 countries around the world. WorldStrides offers experiential learning programs in educational travel, performing arts, language immersion, career exploration, service-learning, study abroad, and sports. Each of these experiences helps students to see beyond the classroom and to see the world ‚Äì and themselves ‚Äì in new ways. www.worldstrides.com

resumen:
For over 25 years, Globalsat Group has been at the forefront of mobile satellite services (MSS) across the Americas, serving a broad spectrum of industries including energy, government, defense, media, mining, finance, agriculture, NGOs, and tourism. Our solutions are designed to support mission-critical operations where seamless connectivity is essential.

We are driven by a commitment to leverage satellite technology for social and environmental impact. Our dedication has been recognized with the prestigious MSUA Satellite Mobility Innovation Award for two consecutive years, in 2023 and 2024.

Globalsat Group simplifies market access and logistics for our partners and clients across the Pan-American region. With a US distribution hub and a network of offices spanning the US, Argentina, Bolivia, Brazil, Central America & the Caribbean, Chile, Colombia, Ecuador, Mexico, and Peru, we ensure our customers receive reliable and effective support wherever they operate.

At the heart of Globalsat Group is a people-first philosophy. Our core values‚Äîtrust, customer focus, and innovation‚Äîguide us in delivering superior service. This client-centered approach has not only garnered industry recognition, such as the "Top Land Mobility Satcom Innovation Award" and Frost & Sullivan's "Latin American Satellite Communications Company of the Year" on multiple occasions, but also the trust of our clients.

As we celebrate our 25th anniversary in 2024, we extend our heartfelt gratitude to our partners, colleagues, and customers who have been integral to our journey of innovation. Looking ahead, Globalsat Group remains committed to expanding our reach and delivering world-class satellite communication services to businesses and governments worldwide.

resumen:
The Mexican Electronics Telecommunications and Information Technologies Industries Chamber has more than 25 years in our country and is an entity representing the Electronics, Telecommunications and Information Tecnology Sector in Mexico, which promotes the development of said sector in a global environment with high quality services.

CANIETI is a public interest, autonomous institution with legal status and capital of its own, different from that of its members, established according to what is provided in the Act of Business Chambers and their Confederations.

Our main objective is to achieve the competitive development of the National Industry with a guild sense and social responsibility.

Individuals or corporations legally established both in the Mexican Republic and abroad, usually engaged in activities related to the electronics, telecommunications or informatics sectors, affiliate in CANIETI.

The Chamber is made up by more than 1000 member companies all over Mexico, gathered to defend and watch their rights and common interests. 

In 2003, 2004, 2006 and 2077 CANIETI received the National Prize of Ethics and Values awarded by the National Confederation of Industrial Chambers (CONCAMIN) to the body that shows commitment and social responsibility both for its members and the society in general.

History
- 1935  Association of Radio Distributors of Mexico City 
- 1940  Mexican Association of Radio Industrialists 
- 1945  Mexican Association of Radio and Television 
- 1950  National Association of the Electronics Industry  
- 1957  National Chamber of the Electronics and Electric Communications Industries. CANIECE 
- 1997  National Chamber of the Electronics, Telecommunications and Informatics Industry, CANIETI 
- 2007  Mexican Electronics Telecommunications and Information Technologies Industries Chamber, CANIETI.

resumen:
Say hello to Diatoms.

Microscopic plants called Diatoms absorb 10-20 billion tonnes of carbon dioxide (CO2) every year. That's equal to the amount of carbon captured annually by all of the world's rainforests.

Diatoms are considered the largest primary producers of oxygen on our planet. It is estimated that through photosynthesis, diatoms produce between 20% and 40% of the oxygen we breathe.

With the campaign "Keeping the Planet cool with Diatoms" we are trying to raise awareness about Diatom potential in CO2 removal.

We are in the process of removing 10GtCO2 by accelerating the growth of native diatoms in polluted open water systems.

resumen:
Origen Tech is a US-based SAP consulting and products development firm focused on helping multinational companies (MNC‚Äôs) to successfully deploy SAP software in a true SaaS-based fashion, as the leading solutions provider for tax and reporting compliance as well as foreign trade process management for companies that run SAP in all the major economies in the region: USA, Brazil, Mexico, Colombia, Peru, Chile, Argentina, etc.

At Origen Tech, we integrate all aspects of cloud-enabled SAP solutions  for companies that have traditionally seen SAP as too expensive from a software license, deployment, and a sustainability perspective.

Through the adoption of cloud based intelligent enterprise software, state of the art AI technology and a solid repository of innovations combined with an agile approach, we empower organizations looking to scale. Origen Tech also support entrepreneurs, small and minority owned business who are looking for transformative ERP solutions to run their business on a modern and cloud-based platform. 

As a strategic systems integrator and application support specialist, we are uniquely positioned to handle the complex business environments of multinational corporations with specific expertise in LATAM & Brazil SAP localization projects, compliance, global trade, etc. We are distinguished as a ‚ÄúBest in Class‚Äù SAP partner providing comprehensive end-to-end SAP products, solutions, and consulting services from SMBs to Fortune 500 companies.

Origen‚Äôs culturally diverse team brings a practical hands-on approach to addressing complex business issues such as fiscal & statutory regulations and supply chain optimization with global, regional, and local consulting competencies. We help our clients achieve operational improvements by using a collaborative approach of aligning the IT strategy of the company with the goals of the business ensuring that our customers gain a competitive advantage in the marketplace with sustainable and compliant operations.

resumen:
We make it possible for international student-athletes to combine college sports and higher education in the US and Canada. We connect international student-athletes with US and Canadian colleges and universities, offering game-changing college sports recruiting solutions for students, parents, coaches, and universities. 

Our team of 100+ full-time staff across 10 countries are, for the most part, former student-athletes. We know what it takes to go on the student-athlete journey with a scholarship, the challenges and opportunities before starting, during the college years, and after graduation. 

Together, we have developed an unmatched college coach network and have helped over 14,100 student-athletes over the years, from a wide variety of sports to more than 820 schools in all 50 US states and Canada. 

Our student-athletes typically receive a combination of sports scholarships, academic scholarships, and international scholarships. We have gained over 796 million USD in scholarships for our students, and have enabled and witnessed amazing, life-changing experiences while being part of their college journey. 

Keystone Sports is the sports division of Keystone Education Group. We have united Europe's most established international college sports recruiting agencies under one roof: 

AGM (Spain & LatAm)
CMAS (Mexico)
College Scholarships USA (Scandinavia + UK/Ireland/Australia/New Zealand)
Future Elite Sports (UK)
Sport-Scholarships (Germany, Austria, Switzerland)
Tennis Smart (UK & USA)
uniexperts (Germany, Austria, Switzerland)

We are proud of our legacy, and we are truly excited about the future of the college sports recruitment industry and the positive impact we‚Äôre creating through Keystone Sports. 

What's your journey?

resumen:
AGOL Worldwide is a time-critical logistics and Global Trade company specializing in the Aviation, Automotive, Information Technology, and Telecom industries.

We provide our clients with end-to-end supply chain and transportation solutions that ensure the timely and cost-effective delivery of their products and services.

Our Services

üì¶ Importer Of Record

AGOL Worldwide offers global IT and telecom companies a one-stop solution for their Importer of Record (IOR) needs, with white-glove delivery and import compliance certification services available in over 120 countries. We provide end-to-end solutions and exceptional service quality to ensure timely and efficient delivery of goods while complying with all relevant regulations.

üöö On-board Courier

AGOL Worldwide's On-board Courier (OBC) service ensures safe and timely delivery of time-critical shipments, with a focus on reliability, speed, and transparency. Our experienced team provides end-to-end solutions and real-time tracking to meet the unique needs of businesses of all sizes.
 
‚õìÔ∏è Supply Chain Solutions

AGOL Worldwide offers comprehensive and efficient Supply Chain Solutions as a third-party logistics provider. This results in timely delivery of goods, improved supply chain management, and cost savings for our clients.
